-- South Africa Says to End Process for New Transnet Board, Chairman Shortly
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-11-02T15:08:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/south-africa-says-to-end-process-for-new-transnet-board-chairman-shortly.html
South Africa’s Department of Public
Enterprises said the process to appoint a board and a chairman
will be “concluded shortly.”  The new board will oversee the appointment of a new chief
executive officer for the company, Johannesburg-based Transnet
said in an e-mailed statement today. Chris Wells has been acting
as CEO since March last year after Maria Ramos left to join Absa
Group Ltd.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  